class ListNode {
    constructor(val, next = null) {
        this.val = val;
        this.next = next;
    }
}

function numComponents(head, nums) {
    const numSet = new Set(nums);
    let result = 0;
    let connected = false;

    while (head !== null) {
        if (numSet.has(head.val)) {
            if (!connected) {
                connected = true;
                result++;
            }
        } else {
            connected = false;
        }
        head = head.next;
    }

    return result;
}
```


    Algorithm:
1. Create a set of nums.
2. Initialize result to 0 and a flag, connected, to false.
3. Traverse the linked list.
   - If the current node's value is in the set,
      - Check if connected is false,
         - Set connected to true and increment result.
   - Else, set connected to false.
4. Return the result.

